.TH TRYME 1
.SH NAME
tryme \- Ephemeral workspace manager — fuzzy\-searchable, dated experiment directories
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtryme\fR [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A Rust port of tobi/try. The TUI renders on stderr and the chosen action is emitted as a shell script on stdout; the `try` shell function (from `tryme init`) evals it. Conformance target: tobi/try v1.9.3.
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Show help (printed to stderr)
.TP
\fB\-v, \-\-version\fR
Show version (printed to stderr)
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Tries directory (default: ~/src/tries); last occurrence wins
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-colors\fR
Disable ANSI styling (NO_COLOR env is also honored)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-expand\-tokens\fR
Alias of \-\-no\-colors (historical name)
.TP
\fB\-\-and\-exit\fR
Render one frame and exit (test harness)
.TP
\fB\-\-and\-type\fR \fI<VALUE>\fR
Pre\-seed the input buffer (test harness)
.TP
\fB\-\-and\-keys\fR \fI<VALUE>\fR
Inject a key sequence (test harness)
.TP
\fB\-\-and\-confirm\fR \fI<VALUE>\fR
Substitute for delete\-confirmation input; only literal YES confirms (test harness)
.TP
\fB\-\-usage\-spec\fR
Emit the usage KDL spec on stdout and exit
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBinit\fR
Output the `try` shell wrapper function
.TP
\fBinstall\fR
Append the wrapper to your shell rc file (idempotent)
.TP
\fBclone\fR
Clone a git repo into a date\-prefixed try directory
.TP
\fBworktree\fR
Create a detached worktree try from a git repo (or `dir` for the cwd)
.TP
\fBexec\fR
Manual mode: emit the shell script on stdout (what the wrapper calls)
.SH "TRYME INIT"
Output the `try` shell wrapper function
.PP
\fBUsage:\fR tryme init [<ABS_PATH>]
.PP
\fBArguments:\fR
.PP
.TP
\fB<ABS_PATH>\fR
Absolute tries path baked into the wrapper (must start with /)
